# Agent skills routing (token-aware)

This repo has many optional skills under `.cursor/skills/` and `.agents/skills/`.
**Do not open or summarize the whole catalog.** Load at most 1–2 skills per task.

## Always-on (already rules — do not re-read as skills)

- **Ponytail** (`.cursor/rules/ponytail.mdc`): default coding style — YAGNI, shortest correct diff.
- **Headroom** (`.cursor/rules/headroom-compression.mdc`): compress tool output >500 lines before analysis.

## Pick by task (read that skill’s `SKILL.md` only when needed)

| Task | Skill / tool |
|------|----------------|
| Ambiguous feature request | `grill-me`, then `to-spec` / `spec-driven-development` |
| Align with existing ADRs/spec docs | `grill-with-docs` |
| Domain / Money / permissions modeling | `domain-modeling` |
| Implement with tests | `tdd` + `implement` |
| Bug | `diagnosing-bugs` / `debugging-and-error-recovery` |
| Blast radius / rename / “what calls X” | **GitNexus MCP** (`impact`, `context`, `query`) — prefer over multi-grep |
| Large logs / long files / dumps | **Headroom MCP** `headroom_compress` |
| UI / visual polish (provisional F00) | `frontend-design` or `ui-ux-pro-max` / `frontend-ui-engineering` |
| Playwright smoke | `webapp-testing` |
| DESIGN.md / token export | `design-md` |
| Pre-PR quality | `ponytail-review` + `code-review` |
| Ship / release checklist | `shipping-and-launch` |
| Security-sensitive change | `security-and-hardening` |

## Hard skips (installed elsewhere or rejected)

- Do **not** install/activate ECC, Superpowers, Understand-Anything, graphify, or gstack here — they overlap with GitNexus/ponytail or inflate context.
- Karpathy guidelines: **not** installed — ponytail already covers simplicity.

## Output discipline

After coding: skipped abstractions / deps in ≤3 short lines (ponytail). Prefer one runnable check for non-trivial logic.
